On 2011-11-03 15:28 , Noah Levitt wrote:
> P.S. I've updated this page for the new git repository, and to follow my own workflow which is the one I can vouch for: http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/
>
> Noah
>
> On 2011-11-03 14:48 , Noah Levitt wrote:
>> Hello David,
>>
>> So, this looks more like a maven build problem than eclipse. However, the maven output you excerpted isn't enough to tell if there was really a problem. Those INFO messages may be normal. So first things first- did the maven build succeed or fail? If it succeeded, you may only need to right click on heritrix3 and click Refresh in eclipse, for it to notice the missing jars.
>>
>> If the maven build did fail, and the reason is that it was unable to download some of the dependency jars, then that is puzzling. For one thing it should be looking in the central repo http://repo1.maven.org/maven2/. For another all the dependencies should be in our repo http://builds.archive.org:8080/maven2/. (If they weren't there when you tried this the other day, I think they should be now.) What version of maven? If you continue to have this problem please send your full maven output.
>>
>> By the way the build will run much faster if you skip the tests: mvn -Dmaven.test.skip=true install
>>
>> Noah
>>
